---
alwaysApply: true
---

This project is a TypeScript project and the following applies:
- ALWAYS use double quotes "" for strings and props in React and TypeScript.
- Always end a statement with semicolon ; in React and TypeScript.
- Filenames for both React and Typescript is to be kebab-case.
- PascalCase for types, classes, components, enums.
- When referring to enums im meaning this syntax "const foo = { enum: "enum" } as const;"

All convex server stuff goes in pkg/convex

Casting stuff to any is not allowed, use unknown. If you actually have a use case for "any" I want you to reason it.

Slug paths should use bracketed parameter folder names like [param] or [slug]

Do not export default in react components. We use page.tsx and layout.tsx for actual routes. These either export Page() or Layout() depending on its name.
